%TesML 1.0

=== 'cogdb init' works
--- command: cog init
--- manifest
.git/
node/
index/
index/schema/

=== 'cogdb new <type>' works
--- command: cog new Schema




=== Basic Usage
> cogdb init foo-cog
> cd foo-cog
> cog add Schema
Node *a4gh-0 type(Schema) added
.0 revision is a placeholder node. id has been secured.
> cog edit a4gh
.enter vim with a text representation of the node
.user sets Type to 'foo'
.user sets Base to 'CogNode'
.user adds fields for 'foo' type
.on save adds to cogdb
> cog add foo
Node *7ud3 type(foo) added
.cogdb will not allow you to add type 'bar' since schema doesn't exist yet

Questions?
